    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2662945341" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2662945341" />
    <a title="Teri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3052770-teri"><img alt="Teri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1415823771p2/3052770.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2662945341?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Teri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Teri" href="/user/show/3052770-teri">Teri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3052770-teri?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3052770-teri?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3052770-teri?shelf=pulitzer-2019">pulitzer-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2662945341" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4886488259369467417">This is a very well-written, readable, comprehensive single-volume compendium on the Civil War. McPherson begins in the mid-19th century detailing the events leading up to the war including Lincoln&apos;s rise in politics, the Dred Scott decision, and Harper&apos;s Ferry. He covers the causes, the political and social climate, and the economic outlook of the times. Interspersed between the various battles of the war, McPherson covers specific side information such as conscription, medical needs, POW priso</span>
  <span id="freeText4886488259369467417" style="display:none">This is a very well-written, readable, comprehensive single-volume compendium on the Civil War. McPherson begins in the mid-19th century detailing the events leading up to the war including Lincoln's rise in politics, the Dred Scott decision, and Harper's Ferry. He covers the causes, the political and social climate, and the economic outlook of the times. Interspersed between the various battles of the war, McPherson covers specific side information such as conscription, medical needs, POW prisons, and data on retention and desertion of troops.<br /><br />This is a great go-to book on all things related to the Civil War that I'm sure I'll reference many times.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4886488259369467417" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

